Testing the CharFun Package

Me

July 13, 2020

Steps

  1. obtain MGF
  2. replace all instances of \(t\) with \(it\) (that is, \(i\) being the imaginary unit \(\sqrt{-1}\))
    • this turns the moment generating function into a characteristic function

Setup

# install.packages("Bessel")
# library(CharFun)
library(MyCharFun)

Simple example (from the documentation)

char1 <- function(t) exp(-t^2 / 2) # this is the characteristic function for the standard normal dist
result1 <- cf2DistGP(char1)

# res1 <- matrix(c(result1$xMean, result1$xStd^2), ncol=1)
# rownames(res1) <- c("Mean:", "Variance:")
# colnames(res1) <- c("")
# res1

A better example from 0 Review Practice, problem 3(a)

char_a <- function(t) 1/(1 - 6*complex(imaginary = t))^5
result_a <- cf2DistGP(char_a)

# res_a <- matrix(c(result_a$xMean, result_a$xStd^2), ncol=1)
